== Objective 
One of the major requirements for this project is to be able to completely manufacture a full heat exchanger (1000 glued modules) within a single 8-hour working day. The following procedures can be used to estimate construction time based on a smaller sample of completed plates.

== Test Design
The following testing procedure is a wet run of the system, meaning adhesive will be used in the test. A similar test can be run without adhesive (dry test), with slight modifications to the following testing procedures. 

+ Fully assemble the system, including putting adhesive in the roller tray and preparing all necessary materials.
+ Begin a stopwatch at the beginning of the test cycle period.
+ Turn on the switch to power the motor.
+ Place the lamina into the lamina jig using the location features.  
+ Insert two MPHX plates into a jig and hand-feed the MPHX jig until the rollers catch. 
+ After the plates have been fully coated by the roller, pull the jig through the rest of the feed and turn it over. Place the MPHX jig on top of the lamina jig and align with the locating features.
+ Repeat Steps 3-6 four more times, stacking the previous completed plate-lamina-jig module on top of the previous one, aligning it via the alignment pins on each jig. Turn off the motor for the glue application rollers.
+ 5 minutes after completing the final glue application cycle, remove all plates from the jig stack and set aside.
+ Stop the timer and multiply the amount of time it took to complete ten cycles by 100 to estimate the amount of time it would take to complete 1000 plate assemblies. Record the multiplied amount of time to be used later.
+ Record the time needed to thoroughly clean all glue application components.
+ Add one hour (to account for breaks taken throughout the work day) to the combined estimated 1000 plate completion time and time to clean the roller components. This is the final length of a workday required to complete a full heat exchanger device via our glue application system.

== Data Collection
This test will measure an approximate time to successfully manufacture a full heat exchanger of 1000 completed plate-lamina modules. This will be done by extrapolating the time it takes to complete 10 plates, which will be measured via a stopwatch. The purpose of this collection is to decide if a user of our device would be able to complete a full heat exchanger in an 8 hour work day as per the design requirements.

== Data Analysis
For proper estimation of the average time needed to complete a full heat exchanger, this test should be repeated at least 3 times, with a final estimated time to complete a full heat exchanger being an average of those test times. Should the final average of times be significantly longer than 8 hours, further design optimization may be necessary.

